UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1857
1 AN ACT relating to artificial intelligence and declaring an emergency.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 367 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 As used in Sections 1 to 3 of this Act:
6 (1) "Administrative support":
7 (a) Means tasks performed to assist a licensed professional in the delivery of
8 therapy or psychotherapy services that do not involve therapeutic
9 communication; and
10 (b) Includes but is not limited to:
11 1. Managing appointment scheduling and reminders;
12 2. Processing billing and insurance claims; and
13 3. Drafting general communications related to therapy logistics that do
14 not include therapeutic communication or advice;
15 (2) "Artificial intelligence" has the same meaning as in KRS 42.722;
16 (3) "Consent":
17 (a) Means a clear, explicit affirmative act by an individual that:
18 1. Unambiguously communicates the individual's express, freely given,
19 informed, voluntary, specific, and unambiguous written agreement,
20 including a written agreement provided by electronic means; and
21 2. Is revocable by the individual; and
22 (b) Does not include an agreement that is obtained by:
23 1. The acceptance of a general or broad terms of use agreement or a
24 similar document that contains descriptions of artificial intelligence
25 along with other unrelated information;
26 2. An individual hovering over, muting, pausing, or closing a given piece
27 of digital content; or
Page 1 of 6
